    <section class="tips">
        <h2>Top Cybersecurity Tips</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Use strong and unique passwords for all accounts.</li>
            <li>Enable two-factor authentication wherever possible.</li>
            <li>Be cautious with email attachments and links.</li>
            <li>Update your software regularly to patch vulnerabilities.</li>
            <li>Use antivirus and firewall protection.</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    
    <section class="threats">
        <h2>Common Cybersecurity Threats</h2>
        <div class="threat">
            <h3>Phishing</h3>
            <p>Scammers use fake messages to steal your personal information. Always verify the source before clicking links.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="threat">
            <h3>Malware</h3>
            <p>Malicious software can harm your device. Avoid downloading unknown attachments or visiting untrustworthy websites.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="threat">
            <h3>Ransomware</h3>
            <p>Attackers lock your data and demand payment to release it. Keep backups of important files to stay protected.</p>
        </div>
    </section>

    
